{
  "page": "Wun Weg Wun Dar Wun",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Wun Weg Wun Dar Wun</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Wun_Wun.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Wun Wun.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/bf/Wun_Wun.jpg/350px-Wun_Wun.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"511\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/bf/Wun_Wun.jpg/525px-Wun_Wun.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/bf/Wun_Wun.jpg/700px-Wun_Wun.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Art by Aleksandar Radovanovic</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nWun Wun</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Race</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Giants\" title=\"Giants\">Giant</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">Beyond the Wall</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appears)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">Played by</span></th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/List_of_actors_of_the_televised_series#Ian_Whyte.2C_Wun_Weg_Wun_Dar_Wun\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"List of actors of the televised series\">Ian Whyte</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span style=\"white-space:nowrap\">TV series</span></th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>: <a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_5\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 5\">Season 5</a> | <a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones_-_Season_6\" title=\"Game of Thrones - Season 6\">6</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Wun Weg Wun Dar Wun</b>, nicknamed <b>Wun Wun</b>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is a <a href=\"/index.php/Giants\" title=\"Giants\">giant</a> who lives <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>, Wun Wun is portrayed by Ian Whyte.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes_by_Wun_Wun\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes by Wun Wun</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Wun_Wun\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Wun Wun</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wun_Weg_Wun_Dar_Wun&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl><dd><i>See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Wun_Weg_Wun_Dar_Wun\" title=\"Category:Images of Wun Weg Wun Dar Wun\">Images of Wun Weg Wun Dar Wun</a></i></dd></dl>\n<p>Wun Wun is at least fourteen feet tall, even larger than <a href=\"/index.php/Mag_Mar_Tun_Doh_Weg\" title=\"Mag Mar Tun Doh Weg\">Mag the Mighty</a>, and he possesses the strength of twelve men.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He has hands as large as hams<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and big square teeth.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Wun Wun is a vegetarian who enjoys roots, onions, turnips, and raw neeps,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and he also likes roast vegetables.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> A speaker of the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Tongue\" title=\"Old Tongue\">Old Tongue</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> the giant's voice sounds like a tumbling boulder and his laughter is a roar.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Whilst typically passive, Wun Wun will lash out if provoked.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> His oaken maul is six feet long with a stone head the size of a loaf of bread.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wun_Weg_Wun_Dar_Wun&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wun_Weg_Wun_Dar_Wun&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Along with some <a href=\"/index.php/Wildlings\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wildlings\">wildlings</a>, Wun Weg Wun Dar Wun is discovered when <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Night&#39;s Watch\">Lord Commander</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a>, leads new recruits to the <a href=\"/index.php/Weirwood_grove\" title=\"Weirwood grove\">weirwood grove</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Haunted_forest\" title=\"Haunted forest\">haunted forest</a>. With the help of some diplomacy by the new wildling recruit <a href=\"/index.php/Leathers\" title=\"Leathers\">Leathers</a>, they avoid a fight and manage to convince the wildlings to return with them to <a href=\"/index.php/Castle_Black\" title=\"Castle Black\">Castle Black</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Leathers calls the giant Wun Wun.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Jon speaks with Wun Wun as often as he can, with the help of Leathers, learning more about giants and their stories.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Wun Wun had never tasted <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a> before he came to Castle Black, but he develops a liking for it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The giant sleeps in the entry hall of <a href=\"/index.php/Hardin%27s_Tower\" title=\"Hardin&#39;s Tower\">Hardin's Tower</a>, and he guards <a href=\"/index.php/Val\" title=\"Val\">Val</a> when she moves into the tower.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Selyse_Florent\" title=\"Selyse Florent\">Selyse</a> arrives at Castle Black, Wun Wun kneels in front of her and Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Shireen_Baratheon\" title=\"Shireen Baratheon\">Shireen</a>, who is fascinated by the giant. Wun Wun is distracted by <a href=\"/index.php/Patchface\" title=\"Patchface\">Patchface</a>, who jumps away and falls over into a snowdrift. Wun Wun laughs loudly, which causes Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Patrek_of_King%27s_Mountain\" title=\"Patrek of King&#39;s Mountain\">Patrek of King's Mountain</a> to draw his sword.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Selyse and the <a href=\"/index.php/Queen%27s_men\" title=\"Queen&#39;s men\">queen's men</a> are displeased by the giant's presence.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Jon receives <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard_Letter\" title=\"Bastard Letter\">a letter</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Snow\" title=\"Ramsay Snow\">Ramsay Bolton</a>, he hears Wun Wun roar and a man scream. When he arrives at Hardin's Tower, Jon finds a bleeding Wun Wun smashing a dead Patrek against a tower wall. While he is distracted by Wun Wun's rage, the men of the Watch turn on Jon and stab him repeatedly, chanting \"For the Watch\" as they attempt to assassinate him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_by_Wun_Wun\">Quotes by Wun Wun</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wun_Weg_Wun_Dar_Wun&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes by Wun Wun\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Wun Wun</b>: Kneel queen. Little queen.<br />\n<b>Shireen</b>: He's a <a href=\"/index.php/Giant\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Giant\">giant</a>! A real true giant, like from the stories.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Wun Wun and <a href=\"/index.php/Shireen_Baratheon\" title=\"Shireen Baratheon\">Shireen Baratheon</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Wun_Wun\">Quotes about Wun Wun</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wun_Weg_Wun_Dar_Wun&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Wun Wun\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>His name is Wun Weg Wun Dar Wun, <a href=\"/index.php/Leathers\" title=\"Leathers\">Leathers</a> tells me. A lot to wrap a tongue around, I know. Leathers calls him Wun Wun, and that seems to serve.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Othell_Yarwyck\" title=\"Othell Yarwyck\">Othell Yarwyck</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>He reminded Jon of <a href=\"/index.php/Hodor\" title=\"Hodor\">Hodor</a>. Hodor twice as big, twice as strong, and half as clever.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a>'s thoughts</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I had been given to understand that the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> defended <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">the realm</a> against such monsters. No one mentioned keeping them as pets.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Patrek_of_King%27s_Mountain\" title=\"Patrek of King&#39;s Mountain\">Patrek of King's Mountain</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>A <a href=\"/index.php/Giants\" title=\"Giants\">giant</a> as protector? Even <a href=\"/index.php/Dalla\" title=\"Dalla\">Dalla</a> could not boast of that.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Val\" title=\"Val\">Val</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wun_Weg_Wun_Dar_Wun&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Wun Wun kills <a href=\"/index.php/Patrek_of_King%27s_Mountain\" title=\"Patrek of King&#39;s Mountain\">Patrek of King's Mountain</a> to fulfill a bet that <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> made with his friend, Patrick St. Denis. George is a fan of the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_Giants\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:New York Giants\">New York Giants</a> football team, while Patrick supports the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dallas_Cowboys\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Dallas Cowboys\">Dallas Cowboys</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Wun Wun is named after <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phil_Simms\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Phil Simms\">Phil Simms</a>, a quarterback for the Giants who wore #11.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wun_Weg_Wun_Dar_Wun&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\">1.7</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\">1.8</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\">1.9</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_39\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 39\">Chapter 39</a>, Jon VIII.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radw